      <p>When the documented steps don&rsquo;t hold, the cause is usually past the surface &mdash; conflicting hosting where more than one computer claims the file, a stale lock from a session that crashed, a read-only network path or permissions problem, or a company file living on a synced (Dropbox/OneDrive) folder that keeps re-locking it. A Certified ProAdvisor with active Desktop and Enterprise certifications diagnoses the actual root cause, corrects the hosting or storage setup against a written scope, and verifies the file opens cleanly for the right users before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
